    "macroSummary": "Markets are rallying on diplomatic optimism around US-Iran peace talks and Israel-Lebanon ceasefire discussions, driving risk-on flows with dollar weakness, falling oil prices, and rising gold. The peace dividend theme is creating disinflationary tailwinds that could extend the current relief rally, though crypto technicals show mixed signals with Bitcoin facing resistance at $76K while Ethereum shows bullish momentum.",
    "regimeImpact": "The diplomatic breakthrough creates a more favorable backdrop for the relief rally to continue, potentially extending duration and reducing near-term volatility as geopolitical risk premiums compress.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Monitor BMNR ladder strikes as Bitcoin tests $75-76K resistance zone with increased volatility and potential German government selling pressure",
      "Consider reducing short book exposure on energy names as oil falls below key levels and peace premium unwinds",
      "Maintain Maturity sector overweight as falling yields and risk-on flows favor defensive positioning in current relief rally"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Dollar at six-week lows signals continued risk-on momentum supporting relief rally thesis.",
